  <h2 id="customer-experience">Customer Experience</h2>
  <p>
    Beyond coverage and pricing, how does it feel to use these insurance products? Both are established American insurers with professional service cultures.
  </p>

  <h3>Digital Experience</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>Cigna Global</strong> offers an excellent digital experience. Their mobile app and member portal are intuitive, modern, and feature-rich. Finding providers, submitting claims, tracking status, and accessing ID cards are all straightforward. Among international insurers, Cigna's digital tools are consistently rated best-in-class.
  </p>
  <p>
    <strong>Aetna International</strong> provides functional digital tools that get the job done. The app and portal work well, though they feel slightly less polished than Cigna's. US-based features integrate smoothly with domestic Aetna tools.
  </p>

  <h3>Member Satisfaction</h3>
  <p>
    Cigna Global receives consistently positive reviews for customer service and claims handling. Members appreciate responsive support and generally smooth experiences. Common praise focuses on helpful representatives and reasonable claims processing.
  </p>
  <p>
    Aetna International receives solid reviews, with particular praise for US coverage integration. Members who use US healthcare regularly appreciate the seamless experience. Some reviews note less personalized service compared to Cigna.
  </p>

  <h3>Renewal Experience</h3>
  <p>
    Both providers increase premiums at annual renewal, reflecting age increases and general healthcare inflation. Neither is known for dramatic surprise increases, but expect 5-10% annual premium growth.
  </p>
  <p>
    Neither provider offers no-claims discounts. Healthy members who rarely claim pay the same as frequent users.
  </p>

